00:18:51,630 --> 00:18:52,506
Good morning.

250
00:18:53,432 --> 00:18:54,740
Where can I charge my phone?

251
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:57,838
- Lulu. Lulu, assistance please.
- Can I charge my phone?

252
00:18:57,903 --> 00:18:59,644
Yes, Ma'am.
I'll do it for you, Ma'am.

253
00:18:59,705 --> 00:19:00,513
Thank you.

254
00:19:05,210 --> 00:19:08,214
Ma'am, Ma'am. What happened, Ma'am?
Can I help you, Ma'am?

255
00:19:08,280 --> 00:19:10,123
No, I'm fine.
There was an insect.

256
00:19:10,182 --> 00:19:11,422
It's gone now.

257
00:19:11,750 --> 00:19:12,888
Lulu, fix it.

258
00:19:13,051 --> 00:19:14,155
Thank you very much.

259
00:19:14,219 --> 00:19:15,789
Cleaning. Cleaning.
Cleaning. Go, girl.

260
00:19:16,221 --> 00:19:17,495
By the way, these are my sons.

261
00:19:17,556 --> 00:19:19,365
Rommel and...

262
00:19:19,625 --> 00:19:20,695
- Hi, Rommel.
- Rommel.

263
00:19:28,367 --> 00:19:32,474
Snob. Unlike the other one. Friendly.

264
00:19:34,306 --> 00:19:38,345
Ma'am, please forgive my daughter.
Her father's an alien.

265
00:19:38,410 --> 00:19:40,481
And who's the alien's mommy?

266
00:19:41,213 --> 00:19:43,887
Your daughter's funny. Very energetic.

267
00:19:44,683 --> 00:19:49,462
Oh, yes. I'm so proud of her.
Very proud.

268
00:20:27,526 --> 00:20:30,996
Eight steps forward. One to the left.

269
00:21:24,750 --> 00:21:26,525
Rommel, where are you going?

270
00:21:26,585 --> 00:21:28,155
Just gonna go out.

271
00:21:31,757 --> 00:21:35,705
Mom, why do you think Rommel
changed after the accident?

272
00:21:58,050 --> 00:21:59,154
Do you see it?

273
00:22:00,952 --> 00:22:01,828
Yes.

274
00:22:02,254 --> 00:22:03,460
I don't.

275
00:22:04,089 --> 00:22:06,695
Well, it's because
you're blind, isn't it?

276
00:22:07,159 --> 00:22:10,333
More often since you arrived.

277
00:22:11,196 --> 00:22:14,507
Looks like there are
guests checking in.

278
00:22:15,500 --> 00:22:19,141
That's good.
it's not just a café anymore.

279
00:22:22,107 --> 00:22:24,053
I'm already sleepy, Babe.

280
00:22:24,109 --> 00:22:25,645
Let's go to sleep then.

281
00:22:36,922 --> 00:22:41,598
Let's go. Your mother's
looking for you. Let's go home.

282
00:22:51,403 --> 00:22:52,381
Babe.

283
00:22:52,437 --> 00:22:53,609
Babe...

284
00:22:54,606 --> 00:22:57,450
- I thought we're just going to sleep?
- Yeah, in a bit.

285
00:22:58,110 --> 00:23:00,556
- I'm tired.
- No, it'll be fine.

286
00:23:01,012 --> 00:23:02,252
- Babe, I'm tired.
- Come on.

287
00:23:02,314 --> 00:23:05,591
Babe, I said
I'm tired from work, okay?

288
00:23:05,650 --> 00:23:08,392
- Why did you push me?
- You're tired?

289
00:23:09,087 --> 00:23:10,191
What do you want?

290
00:23:15,327 --> 00:23:17,170
Why did you hit me?

291
00:23:17,229 --> 00:23:19,539
This is what you want, isn't it?

292
00:23:20,031 --> 00:23:21,203
Ouch!

293
00:23:21,733 --> 00:23:25,112
- Come on. Please?
- Fine. I'll just take a shower.

294
00:23:25,270 --> 00:23:26,613
Hurry up.

295
00:23:32,310 --> 00:23:34,415
Babe, hurry it up.

296
00:23:34,479 --> 00:23:36,220
Just a second.

297
00:23:47,726 --> 00:23:53,677
- Babe, let's go. Hurry, hurry.
- Why, babe? What is it?

298
00:23:53,732 --> 00:23:55,473
Hold on, Babe.
I'll just put my clothes on.

299
00:23:55,534 --> 00:23:57,138
No, let's go. Come on!

300
00:24:01,173 --> 00:24:02,652
We'll never come back here again.

301
00:24:02,707 --> 00:24:05,210
Thank you. And please come again.

302
00:24:27,632 --> 00:24:35,073
Sir Edu, we saw a dead body
while on our way here yesterday.

303
00:24:35,607 --> 00:24:37,382
That was our neighbor.

304
00:24:38,910 --> 00:24:44,155
It was Carding.
He raped his fifteen year old daughter.

305
00:24:46,852 --> 00:24:49,423
The killer must have been very angry.

306
00:24:50,088 --> 00:24:51,692
His face was crushed.

307
00:24:52,057 --> 00:24:54,298
Many have died here.

308
00:24:54,993 --> 00:24:57,132
They say all of them were rapists.

309
00:24:57,195 --> 00:25:01,940
They say a rape victim's ghost
is the killer.

310
00:25:02,434 --> 00:25:07,110
They say she made a deal with
dark forces to seek revenge.

311
00:25:12,410 --> 00:25:15,789
Wow, Sir Edu, where did you hear that?

312
00:25:15,914 --> 00:25:17,086
From your ancestors?

313
00:25:17,983 --> 00:25:20,054
You're kidding.

314
00:25:20,452 --> 00:25:22,056
- "Dark forces".
- Here.

315
00:25:22,454 --> 00:25:25,765
Pinoy Ghost Tales Volume 8

316
00:25:26,558 --> 00:25:28,003
Later, son.

317
00:26:09,935 --> 00:26:12,415
Don't go in there.
She's always there.

318
00:26:14,072 --> 00:26:18,111
Oh, you rascal, always seeing things.
You're like a cop sniffing around.

319
00:26:18,977 --> 00:26:21,287
Ma'am, are you okay?

320
00:26:22,047 --> 00:26:22,855
I'm okay.

321
00:26:26,217 --> 00:26:30,825
Ma'am that's just the wind.
it's the wind.

322
00:26:32,524 --> 00:26:33,798
Oh, you.

323
00:26:40,265 --> 00:26:43,144
Mom, you'll feel better in a while.

324
00:26:46,304 --> 00:26:47,942
Ma'am what's that for?

325
00:26:49,507 --> 00:26:51,009
Stress reliever?

326
00:26:54,913 --> 00:26:57,951
Yeah. My doctor diagnosed me...

327
00:26:58,016 --> 00:27:01,725
with post-traumatic stress disorder
after the accident.

328
00:27:03,355 --> 00:27:07,701
I can't relax. I can't stay calm.
I get paranoid.

329
00:27:08,026 --> 00:27:09,232
Hallucinations.

330
00:27:09,294 --> 00:27:12,138
Hallucinachon.

331
00:27:12,197 --> 00:27:15,144
Not hallucinachon, mommy.
Hallucination.

332
00:27:15,200 --> 00:27:18,079
It's the same thing, you silly kid.

333
00:27:19,104 --> 00:27:22,278
Ma'am this is Sgt. Villegas.

334
00:27:26,244 --> 00:27:27,348
Mrs. Calderon.

335
00:27:28,847 --> 00:27:30,918
- SPO4 Caldo.
- Hi. Good morning.

336
00:27:31,549 --> 00:27:34,496
- Coffee. Please sit down.
- Thank you.

337
00:27:35,053 --> 00:27:37,033
To what do I owe the pleasure
of your presence, Sergeant?

338
00:27:37,088 --> 00:27:38,863
Yes, Ma'am.

339
00:27:38,990 --> 00:27:42,403
There are a lot of unpleasant
memories in this place.

340
00:27:43,061 --> 00:27:46,406
Just a few days ago,
a man was brutally murdered.

341
00:27:46,831 --> 00:27:50,335
He was accused of sexually
abusing his teenage daughter.

342
00:27:51,936 --> 00:27:53,313
You'll be living here?

343
00:27:55,640 --> 00:27:58,280
Yes, Aunt Lola asked me to work here.

344
00:27:58,343 --> 00:28:02,291
And my children have fond memories
in this pension house.

345
00:28:02,347 --> 00:28:05,692
Please be careful.
There are a lot of murder cases here.

346
00:28:07,185 --> 00:28:08,960
Sir, there's an update on the case.

347
00:28:10,588 --> 00:28:14,661
Let's go. We'll go ahead, ma'am.
Thank you for the coffee.

348
00:28:15,360 --> 00:28:17,670
If there's anything...
just call me in the station.

349
00:28:17,729 --> 00:28:20,232
- We'll be going now, Ma'am.
- So, it's really dangerous here.

350
00:28:21,032 --> 00:28:22,170
Please take care.

351
00:28:22,233 --> 00:28:24,008
Yeah, you too.

352
00:28:49,127 --> 00:28:51,164
Help me.

353
00:29:02,140 --> 00:29:03,210
Rommel?

354
00:29:06,711 --> 00:29:07,485
Amiel?

355
00:29:27,932 --> 00:29:29,377
Rommel?

356
00:29:31,603 --> 00:29:32,775
Amiel?

357
00:30:13,478 --> 00:30:14,456
Amiel?

358
00:31:27,185 --> 00:31:28,562
Amiel?

359
00:31:52,677 --> 00:31:56,250
Amiel? Rommel?

360
00:32:21,806 --> 00:32:22,910
Who are you?

361
00:32:25,343 --> 00:32:27,619
What are you doing here?

362
00:32:30,448 --> 00:32:31,859
I'm calling the police.

363
00:32:32,583 --> 00:32:33,687
Who are you?!

364
00:32:38,489 --> 00:32:40,935
Why does God let this happen to us?

365
00:32:41,359 --> 00:32:44,169
Why does He make us choose this Way?

366
00:32:58,676 --> 00:33:02,715
You, Rosa.
He'll be taken away from you. Soon!

367
00:33:34,178 --> 00:33:34,952
Rommel?

368
00:33:37,015 --> 00:33:40,292
Rommel, what are you doing out here?
Why aren't you in bed?

369
00:33:44,989 --> 00:33:46,161
Amiel.

370
00:33:48,693 --> 00:33:50,866
Didn't Rommel go out, Mom?

371
00:33:51,629 --> 00:33:56,100
Oh yeah.

372
00:34:02,306 --> 00:34:03,284
Amiel.

373
00:34:07,445 --> 00:34:09,186
Can you hear anything?

374
00:34:09,847 --> 00:34:14,227
Mom, I'm blind. Not deaf.

375
00:34:18,289 --> 00:34:22,203
You? Do you hear it?

376
00:34:27,331 --> 00:34:29,538
Your bed is calling you.

377
00:34:31,069 --> 00:34:33,913
Go rest. I'll take care of Rommel.

378
00:34:34,639 --> 00:34:35,982
I'll wait for him.

379
00:34:40,678 --> 00:34:41,713
You sure?

380
00:34:47,752 --> 00:34:49,322
Thanks, son.

381
00:34:59,497 --> 00:35:00,942
Miss, which one?

382
00:35:01,032 --> 00:35:02,670
- The one with glasses or the other one?
- The one with glasses.

383
00:35:02,733 --> 00:35:05,577
The one with glasses.
Where's the one with glasses?

384
00:35:05,636 --> 00:35:10,847
Where? Amiel!

385
00:35:11,776 --> 00:35:13,221
Rommel.

386
00:35:23,488 --> 00:35:26,731
- Bro.
- Bro, how are you?

387
00:35:27,091 --> 00:35:28,001
What's up?

388
00:35:28,526 --> 00:35:30,005
Nothing new.

389
00:35:30,061 --> 00:35:33,406
Oh yeah, boys... This is Glen.

390
00:35:34,165 --> 00:35:36,645
This is William.

391
00:35:37,235 --> 00:35:39,647
This stuffs great.

392
00:35:39,904 --> 00:35:42,384
- William's a supplier.
- Are you sure?

393
00:35:43,774 --> 00:35:45,651
Let's go there.

394
00:35:47,011 --> 00:35:49,491
- Where are you going?
- Just here. Come on.

395
00:35:50,915 --> 00:35:52,519
- Dude, nice meeting you.
- Hi, Miss Beautiful.

396
00:35:53,184 --> 00:35:54,026
Can we sit?

397
00:35:54,652 --> 00:35:58,657
Bro, why did you introduce me
to those guys? They're bad influence.

398
00:35:59,390 --> 00:36:00,562
Aren't you gonna talk to us?

399
00:36:01,459 --> 00:36:03,268
Since when have you been
a good boy? Huh?

400
00:36:03,327 --> 00:36:04,704
It's not that.

401
00:36:04,862 --> 00:36:09,038
I just thought, once we moved here,
it would be better if me and my mom...

402
00:36:09,667 --> 00:36:11,578
You know... if we...

403
00:36:11,636 --> 00:36:12,740
Bonded?

404
00:36:13,471 --> 00:36:14,848
To make it up to her?

405
00:36:16,240 --> 00:36:17,685
I'll give you a piece of advice.

406
00:36:18,009 --> 00:36:22,924
The reason your mommy is
unable to move on is because...

407
00:36:22,980 --> 00:36:25,358
you still can't get yourself
to forgive her.

408
00:36:25,616 --> 00:36:27,186
Think about it.

409
00:36:59,417 --> 00:37:02,489
Hey, brother. How are things?

410
00:37:02,553 --> 00:37:04,294
Good, you finally came home.

411
00:37:05,089 --> 00:37:09,560
If mom wakes up and see you
drunk again she'll have a fit.

412
00:37:09,627 --> 00:37:16,545
You know, sometimes I think
I should have been the one...

413
00:37:17,368 --> 00:37:18,813
in your situation.

414
00:37:19,804 --> 00:37:22,250
It hurts too much.

415
00:37:22,673 --> 00:37:24,346
Rommel, what's wrong?

416
00:37:25,309 --> 00:37:26,947
Mom really loves you.

417
00:37:27,712 --> 00:37:29,555
She didn't abandon you.

418
00:37:30,348 --> 00:37:31,452
That's the truth.

419
00:37:42,226 --> 00:37:44,467
Good night, Bro.

420
00:38:01,712 --> 00:38:04,556
Oh, that's beautiful.
Who gave these?

421
00:38:05,283 --> 00:38:06,557
They're from Amanda.

422
00:38:07,318 --> 00:38:08,296
Amanda?

423
00:38:08,352 --> 00:38:11,663
She's outside
waiting for the payment.

424
00:38:23,167 --> 00:38:24,475
Amanda?

425
00:38:26,103 --> 00:38:27,241
Rommel?

426
00:38:28,072 --> 00:38:30,279
Is it really you?

427
00:38:31,776 --> 00:38:34,313
You didn't have a scar
on your forehead before.

428
00:38:36,213 --> 00:38:37,590
You're all grown up.

429
00:38:38,115 --> 00:38:39,389
You too.

430
00:38:41,319 --> 00:38:43,094
Are you still gardening here?

431
00:38:43,954 --> 00:38:45,558
Not anymore.

432
00:38:45,623 --> 00:38:48,968
I sell flowers while waiting
for the next semester.

433
00:38:49,694 --> 00:38:54,404
You know, I never forgot about you.

434
00:38:58,169 --> 00:39:01,981
Rommel and Amanda
have grandkids now.

435
00:39:02,907 --> 00:39:04,284
Wanna see?

436
00:39:05,009 --> 00:39:08,456
Sure. Of course, I do.

437
00:39:14,452 --> 00:39:16,398
- Amanda.
- Hello.

438
00:39:16,454 --> 00:39:19,264
How often do you bring flowers here?

439
00:39:20,691 --> 00:39:22,102
Once a week.

440
00:39:24,228 --> 00:39:25,901
Can you deliver everyday?

441
00:39:26,530 --> 00:39:27,634
Really?

442
00:39:28,232 --> 00:39:31,736
Sure. Is there a specific
kind of flower you like?

443
00:39:31,802 --> 00:39:35,944
- No, you choose for me.
- Okay. Thank you.

444
00:39:36,006 --> 00:39:39,453
So, let's go?
Our grandkids are waiting.

445
00:39:40,211 --> 00:39:41,349
Grandkids?

446
00:39:42,213 --> 00:39:45,490
- Where are you going?
- Not far, mom. Don't worry.

447
00:39:45,783 --> 00:39:47,057
We'll be right back.

448
00:39:50,621 --> 00:39:53,227
Ask permission properly.

449
00:40:03,467 --> 00:40:08,177
We'll just look at the offspring
of the doves I gave her before.

450
00:40:08,739 --> 00:40:10,013
I won't belong.

451
00:40:14,278 --> 00:40:15,916
Don't stay out too late.

452
00:40:19,049 --> 00:40:20,255
Let's go.

453
00:40:34,765 --> 00:40:36,904
That's Rommel's first crush, mom.

454
00:40:38,536 --> 00:40:41,142
She's the reason Rommel
wanted to be circumcised.

455
00:40:42,139 --> 00:40:44,676
Come on! Hurry!
Our grandkids are here.

456
00:40:50,114 --> 00:40:50,922
Wow!

457
00:40:54,885 --> 00:40:58,697
Look. I kept my promise.

458
00:40:59,356 --> 00:41:01,461
I took care of them.

459
00:41:03,060 --> 00:41:06,303
Rommel and Amanda's family
has grown, huh?

460
00:41:10,501 --> 00:41:13,880
I never thought I'd see you again.

461
00:41:15,773 --> 00:41:16,843
I mean them.

462
00:41:18,676 --> 00:41:20,053
Me too.

463
00:41:22,413 --> 00:41:24,222
Once, Rommel got out.

464
00:41:24,882 --> 00:41:27,590
I thought he was gone for good.

465
00:41:29,320 --> 00:41:36,465
But I told Amanda,
"Rommel will come back for you.

466
00:41:37,495 --> 00:41:39,372
He won't leave you.

467
00:41:40,364 --> 00:41:43,402
You'll make many dove children."

468
00:41:44,468 --> 00:41:48,610
That afternoon,
Rommel came back.

469
00:41:49,540 --> 00:41:51,986
And there are now
Twenty-seven of them.

470
00:42:59,176 --> 00:43:00,348
Rosa!

471
00:43:03,480 --> 00:43:04,754
Don't do that.

472
00:43:06,951 --> 00:43:11,798
Rosa.

473
00:43:19,229 --> 00:43:23,678
Mom. Mom.
Mom, what's wrong?

474
00:43:25,336 --> 00:43:30,445
Rommel, I know what happened to her.

475
00:43:31,275 --> 00:43:32,948
She was raped.
Let's help her. Let's save her.

476
00:43:33,010 --> 00:43:37,618
- Mom, it's just a nightmare.
- No. Rommel, please believe me.

477
00:43:38,148 --> 00:43:40,628
The girl who's been haunting me.
She was raped.

478
00:43:40,684 --> 00:43:43,392
She's asking for help. Rommel!

479
00:43:43,654 --> 00:43:45,133
You are so hard-headed.

480
00:43:45,923 --> 00:43:50,872
I told you to drink your medicine.
But you keep forgetting. Here.

481
00:44:09,013 --> 00:44:10,617
Rommel, where's your brother?

482
00:44:12,082 --> 00:44:14,688
Can you check on him
before you go to sleep?

483
00:44:21,959 --> 00:44:26,305
Mom, lie down and sleep.
You're just tired.

484
00:44:38,942 --> 00:44:39,886
Rommel?

485
00:44:43,747 --> 00:44:45,192
I love you.

486
00:44:47,551 --> 00:44:48,894
Go to sleep.

487
00:44:59,096 --> 00:45:00,404
Good morning, Ma'am.

488
00:45:00,464 --> 00:45:05,470
By the Way, I bought candles
for this coming All Souls' Day.

489
00:45:08,038 --> 00:45:12,714
Sir Edu, do you remember
anyone dying here?

490
00:45:12,776 --> 00:45:14,050
Why, ma'am?

491
00:45:15,546 --> 00:45:16,889
Nothing.

492
00:45:16,947 --> 00:45:18,949
It's just that people say
it is bad luck.

493
00:45:19,483 --> 00:45:23,397
It may be why we don't get
a lot of guests in here.

494
00:45:23,454 --> 00:45:26,162
Maybe we need to
have the house blessed.

495
00:45:26,256 --> 00:45:27,132
There was one.

496
00:45:27,191 --> 00:45:30,570
A man died of a heart attack
during a birthday party.

497
00:45:30,627 --> 00:45:32,607
But that was long ago.

498
00:45:32,663 --> 00:45:35,075
A man? How about women?

499
00:45:39,203 --> 00:45:43,015
Ma'am, if you want to know
the history of the pension house...

500
00:45:43,073 --> 00:45:45,952
the previous gardener
knows a lot more.

501
00:45:46,009 --> 00:45:47,420
Sir Pedro.

502
00:45:59,757 --> 00:46:01,236
Anybody ho...

503
00:46:02,860 --> 00:46:04,601
Are you Pedro?

504
00:46:07,197 --> 00:46:08,005
Yes?

505
00:46:09,666 --> 00:46:15,912
The pension house is home
to a restless spirit.

506
00:46:17,307 --> 00:46:19,446
Or maybe it's trapped.

507
00:46:20,110 --> 00:46:21,316
Just like you.

508
00:46:22,045 --> 00:46:24,025
You always have a guardian,
don't you?

509
00:46:24,982 --> 00:46:28,953
I hope one day you'll let it go.

510
00:46:29,019 --> 00:46:30,657
So it can rest in peace.

511
00:46:31,789 --> 00:46:34,360
